Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on modeling image virality using a pairwise neural network. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the study of virality and information diffusion online is a topic gaining traction rapidly in the computational social sciences. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with modeling image virality on online media. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as the paper develops a novel algorithm to model image virality using a pairwise neural network. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as the paper investigates the effect of external category supervision on relative attribute prediction.
